                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1064Visitation">Visitation</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1039Magi">The Three Magi</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref>, (no strings on harp)
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#161v #162r" facs="164">Fols. 161v, 162r</locus>
                        <desc>
                        Eight panels (four per page) containing the Ethiopian warrior saints <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>
                        None of the illuminations contain text. Based on the iconography,
                        panel 7 seems  to show St. Philoteus spearing a brown bull.
                        Based on the presence of a sainted figure to the right of the scene, panel 8 may be depicting St. Mercurius spearing Julian the Apostate and being blessed by St. Basil
                      </desc>
                    </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#162v" facs="165">Fol. 162v</locus>
                        <desc>
                          <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref>, surrounded by four <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s
                        (four in the top of the miniature) and Seven <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref>,
                        including <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> (bottom left)
                        and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName> (bottom, second from right)
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                        <locus target="#179v" facs="182">Fol. 179v</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> surrounded by <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> (four in front of her, one behind and six below),

                        </desc>
                    </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                        <locus target="#180r" facs="182">Fol. 180r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> and a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> seated, flanked by <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>s on either side

                      </desc>
                    </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9">
                        <locus target="#180r" facs="182">Fol. 180r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref> seated wtih the eleven disciples, <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1047Apostles">Apostles Portrait</ref>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10">
                        <locus target="#180v" facs="183">Fol. 180v</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref>, Langinos, the one spearing Jesus in the side, shows both eyes
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d11">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #163r" facs="003 165">folss. 1r, 163r, </locus> (colorful harägs);
                      <locus target="#8v #17r #26r #38r #54r #64r #78r #87v #93v #108v #126r #133r #164r #170r #172r #173r" facs="011 019 028 040 056 066 080 090 096 111 128 135 166 172 174 175">8v, 17r, 26r, 38r, 54r, 64r, 78r, 87v, 93v, 108v, 126r, 133r, 164r, 170r, 172r, 173r, </locus> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#140r #154r #174v" facs="142 156 177">140r, 154r, 174v</locus> (double row of lines of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                          Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#43r #91v #134v #136r" facs="045 094 137 138">folss. 43r, 91v, 134v, 136r, </locus>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#19v #40r #49v #123v" facs="022 042 052 126">19v, 40r, 49v, 123v, </locus>, etc.);
                          and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#13v" facs="016"> f. 13v, line 1</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample
                          room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the
                          line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#4r #21r #22r #26r" facs="006 023 024 028">folss. 4r, 21r, 22r, 26r, </locus>).  Occasionally a line
                          is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#7r #8r #9r #18r" facs="009 010 011 020">7r, 8r, 9r, 18r</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
